#DStv403 #eNCA  JOHANNESBURG - Eskom has implemented Stage 2 blackouts from 5pm on Monday until 5am on Wednesday. Initially, Eskom said the scheduled cuts would start at 9pm. READ: SA's electricity crisis | Eskom names and shames defaulters This morning various stations including Matla and Kendal tripped but the picture worsened dramatically, with the news that Medupi Unit 3 had also broken down. The power supplier is now relying on emergency generation reserves to keep the lights on.  Further development to the #PowerAlert: Medupi Unit 3 broke down a short while ago. This requires Stage 2 loadshedding to be implemented continuously starting at 17:00 this afternoon until 05:00 on Wednesday. https://t.co/l1et1AKPdn